    {
      "id": "sybil_10_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_10",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a mechanically sound 2004 BMW M3, a quintessential analog performance machine. At its heart lies the S54 3.2L atmospheric inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS variable valve timing for a linear power delivery and an 8,000 RPM redline. This example features the desirable Getrag 420G six-speed manual gearbox paired with a factory limited-slip differential. Critical preventative maintenance has been addressed, including rear subframe reinforcement and a VANOS system refresh to ensure long-term structural and mechanical reliability. The chassis retains its signature poise with refreshed bushings and a well-sorted suspension setup that minimizes body roll while maintaining compliance. While the finish shows minor road-going patina, the internals and drivetrain components are in excellent working order, making this a prime candidate for the enthusiast who values tactile feedback and engineering purity.",
